The paper analyzes the performance of the Chord algorithm, which is widely used in computational geometry and graphics. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves analyzing upper and lower bounds, which suggests that it could belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.NA (Numerical Analysis). Additionally, the Chord algorithm is used in optimization, which could place the paper in cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.GR (Computer Graphics).
